____________________________________________________________________________


I'm at the moment being constantly monitored and hindered in sharing Christian material. For instance uTorrent shows that there's three(!) seeders on every torrent I upload when they've been published for a few minutes, and I have shared maybe 1% of the file. How's that possible? A month ago it showed &quot;only&quot; two..

The people who hate what I do block my listening port and slows down my bandwidth to an extreme low, and I'm being bombarded in comments on uploads and mails. The only thing I can do, is to appeal to you who are Christians, to help me seed these torrents, because I don't know how much longer I'm able to do this. Not for long, I fear. And I live in Norway, a so called &quot;free Nation&quot; of the western world..
And then I'm accused of being a &quot;conspiracy-theorist&quot;.. :-)

I've translated the movie about Francisco of Assisi into Norwegian, and in this upload it's not hard subbed, but included as a separate .srt file, so that your DivX player can play it with or without the Norwegian subs. Later on I'll probably both make a hard subbed version, and also a PAL-DVDR-image of the movie..
But for now it's like this. Which is the way most people want it, anyhow.. :-)

But I really need somebody to devote some time and disk-space and bandwidth to seed this further, or else it'll die. I've got no more bandwidth or else my machine gets overloaded and nobody gets anything, really.. Please..?

The movie is directed by Franco Zeffirelli, which a little later on made the movie &quot;Jesus of Nazareth&quot;.

It's obvious that this movie was made during the &quot;flower-power&quot;-period, smack dab in the middle of it, and there are some very soft and dreamy (and of course catholic) sequences now and then. Especially when it comes to the music,  Donovan has made and performs the songs, and one of them I haven't even bothered to translate, since it's so esoteric and &quot;New Age'ish&quot;.

The movie as a whole, though, is a nice contrast to most of the movies made in the times we live in. And most of all the story of the life of Francisco contrasts so many of the so called &quot;men of God&quot; of our age, and their version of the Gospel of Jesus..

Anyway. My intension with this upload is to leave you in a good mood and with the seed and sprout of hope still alive and maybe even watered to grow stronger..

With warm regards to you all and prayers of true peace from the Prince of Peace Himself, Jesus Christ of Nazareth..

